Coach Desiree Ellis and South African team players are welcome by fans during the South African national women's soccer team arrival at OR Tambo International Airport on June 19, 2019 in Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - Banyana Banyana coach Desiree Ellis has been crowned Women's African Coach of the Year. The Confederation of African Football Awards event was held in Egypt on Tuesday night. READ: Banyana Banyana's quest for recognition Ellis' nomination was one of three that came South Africa's way with Thembi Kgatlana nominated in the Women’s African Player of the Year category as well as Banyana Banyana in the Women's National Team of the Year category.